Patch Set 18:

> Patch Set 18:
> 
> Based on the data Tony found about the performance operator only having 4.4 and 4.5 channels that would explain why it doesn't work on 4.6 for me!  I'm removing the channels in my patch and running to see the results.  Thanks everyone!

Actually seems like there is 4.6 for performance-addon-operator. It's really strange, when I looked into it, I was running the commands with a server in 4.5 so it didn't show 4.6, but it does in 4.6:

$ KUBECONFIG=~/clusterconfigs-cluster5/kubeconfig oc version | grep Server
Server Version: 4.6.16

$ KUBECONFIG=~/clusterconfigs-cluster6/kubeconfig oc get packagemanifests performance-addon-operator -o json |     jq  -r '.status.channels[].name'
4.4
4.5
4.6

I think that in any case we shouldn't specify the channel and let it use the default provided by the operator
